  "texts": [
    "While being inclusive of different modeling traditions, from microcircuits to whole-brain network models, conn2res contributes a novel way for researchers to explore the link between structure and function in biological brain networks.",
    "Reservoir computing (RC) is an umbrella term that unifies two computational paradigms, liquid state machines 32 and echo-state networks 36.",
    "The two originated independently in the fields of computational neuroscience and machine-learning, respectively, with a common goal: exploiting the computational properties of complex, nonlinear dynamical systems 37.",
    "However, the ideas encompassed by the RC paradigm had been around in different forms for more than two decades prior [38] [39] [40].",
    "The conventional reservoir computing (RC) architecture consists of an input layer, followed by the reservoir and a readout module (Fig. 1a) 32, 36, 37."
